.TH KDE-FAN-CONTROL-GUI 1 "2026-04-14" "kde-fan-control 1.0.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kde-fan-control-gui \- KDE-native GUI for fan control
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kde-fan-control-gui
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kde-fan-control-gui
is the KDE/Qt6 graphical interface for the KDE Fan Control daemon.
It provides an overview of managed fans, hardware inventory browsing,
per-fan detail editing, a configuration wizard, and system tray
integration with status notifications.
.PP
The GUI must run as a regular user (not root). Privileged
operations such as enrolling fans or applying configuration
changes require polkit authentication, prompted through the
GUI's "Unlock" toolbar button.
.PP
The daemon (\fBkde-fan-control-daemon\fR) must be running on
the system bus for the GUI to function.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B QML2_IMPORT_PATH
Additional QML module search paths. Must include the Kirigami
QML plugin directory if it is not on the default path.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/org.kde.fancontrol.desktop
Desktop entry file.
.TP
.I /usr/share/icons/hicolor/*/apps/org.kde.fancontrol.*
Application icons.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kde-fan-control (1),
.BR kde-fan-control-daemon (8)
